00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:06.680
He lost to a total no-name like you, you know.

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:09.680
If you run away now, you'll be running forever.

00:08:10.280 --> 00:08:10.880
But...

00:08:11.840 --> 00:08:13.840
I wasn't trying to embarrass him.

00:08:14.120 --> 00:08:15.280
Yeah, I know that.

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:17.280
But does he know that, too?

00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:22.520
What am I supposed to do, then?

00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:24.080
Just throw a match or two and let him win.

00:08:24.520 --> 00:08:25.440
Do I really have to do that?

00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:27.120
Or do you want him and his toxic fans

00:08:27.120 --> 00:08:28.680
To keep trashing you for the rest of your life?

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:29.560
You want that?

00:08:29.680 --> 00:08:30.640
That's not too bad...

00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:31.920
Talk some sense into him.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:34.080
You need to decide now,

00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:34.760
Soh.

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:55.920
What's your name?

00:09:15.800 --> 00:09:16.480
Uh...

00:09:18.320 --> 00:09:19.120
It's Soh.

00:09:20.240 --> 00:09:21.320
Thought it was "Derpy."

00:09:21.680 --> 00:09:22.920
Based on your channel name.

00:09:23.520 --> 00:09:24.240
Oh...

00:09:25.280 --> 00:09:27.440
I named it after a gun in a game,

00:09:27.680 --> 00:09:29.080
Derya MK12.

00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:31.560
What a nerd.

00:09:31.600 --> 00:09:33.400
You play a lot of FPS games, P'Three.

00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:34.720
I figured you'd know that.

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:38.560
How dare you!

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:44.840
Derya MK...

00:09:45.680 --> 00:09:46.840
Hearing that name makes me hungry.

00:09:47.760 --> 00:09:49.600
By the way, have you eaten yet?

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:53.240
Not yet.

00:10:01.760 --> 00:10:02.440
Whoa.

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:07.360
Hurry up and eat it.

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:09.280
Really? Can I have this?

00:10:12.360 --> 00:10:13.080
Thank you.

00:10:19.480 --> 00:10:20.560
Because tonight...

00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:23.640
I'm gonna slaughter you in cold blood.

00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:27.400
You won't be able to eat for the next three days.

00:10:50.640 --> 00:10:51.880
(P'Three finally won.)

00:10:53.480 --> 00:10:55.480
(Now that's more like the P'Three we know.)

00:10:57.400 --> 00:11:00.080
(Doesn't anyone else think that damn bear threw the game?)

00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:03.400
(Thought it was just me. He was losing on purpose, wasn't he?)

00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:06.320
(Just look at P'Three's face.)

00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:20.920
That's it.

00:11:21.040 --> 00:11:21.920
It's finally over.

00:11:30.040 --> 00:11:30.720
Wait...

00:11:32.880 --> 00:11:33.680
Now what?

00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:37.680
I'm done with this.

00:11:37.760 --> 00:11:38.840
You damn bear!

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:42.720
You think I, Thr33Gamer, wouldn't notice...

00:11:43.040 --> 00:11:44.400
That you lost on purpose?

00:11:44.640 --> 00:11:46.480
- I didn't lose on purpose. - Liar!

00:11:47.320 --> 00:11:48.200
I'm sorry.

00:11:48.240 --> 00:11:50.240
Fine, I admit it. I let you win on purpose.

00:11:50.240 --> 00:11:51.440
I just wanted you to get your pride back,

00:11:51.480 --> 00:11:53.440
And I was scared of your fans coming for me.

00:11:53.480 --> 00:11:54.600
Get my pride back?

00:11:54.600 --> 00:11:56.200
Are you trying to low-key call me trash,

00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:58.120
Having some kid throw the game so that I could win?

00:11:58.160 --> 00:11:59.360
I'm sorry, P'Three.

00:11:59.640 --> 00:12:01.200
I'll do whatever you want.

00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:02.160
Anything.

00:12:02.240 --> 00:12:03.840
I'll even bark like a dog if you want.

00:12:03.880 --> 00:12:05.160
Well, let me hear it, then.

00:12:05.600 --> 00:12:06.200
Uh...

00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:07.520
Wait...

00:12:08.760 --> 00:12:09.480
Sh*t,

00:12:09.880 --> 00:12:10.680
That was cute.

00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:17.320
Don't you worry, Derpy Kid.

00:12:17.400 --> 00:12:18.160
This time,

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:19.800
I promise you

00:12:19.920 --> 00:12:22.200
There's definitely going to be a rematch.

00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:22.800
No!

00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:25.520
No...

00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:26.680
Please stop.

00:12:26.680 --> 00:12:27.600
I'll teach you a lesson.

00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:28.200
Please don't.

00:12:28.840 --> 00:12:29.520
No.

00:12:30.120 --> 00:12:30.720
No...

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:34.120
No!

00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.520
Sh*t, this salmon is so damn good.

00:12:50.680 --> 00:12:52.120
Thanks for the treat, Soh.

00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:54.600
Your beef with P'Three is over,

00:12:54.680 --> 00:12:56.720
And you made enough from donations to treat us to a buffet.

00:12:56.920 --> 00:12:59.320
Finally, everything's settled, right?

00:13:01.560 --> 00:13:02.040
What?

00:13:13.480 --> 00:13:15.160
Why is the salmon so spicy?

00:13:16.120 --> 00:13:17.440
Are you alright, Soh?

00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:19.400
You've been zoning out all day.

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:23.200
I was just thinking about someone.

00:13:23.480 --> 00:13:24.360
Thinking about someone?

00:13:31.440 --> 00:13:33.120
- Who were you thinking about? - Yeah, who?

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:36.800
Well,

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:39.400
It's P'Three.

00:13:39.440 --> 00:13:41.000
- What? You were thinking about P'Three? - What? You were thinking about P'Three?

00:13:45.560 --> 00:13:48.080
- Oh, look at you. - I knew it.

00:13:48.200 --> 00:13:48.960
No.

00:13:49.840 --> 00:13:50.600
It's not like that.

00:13:51.800 --> 00:13:53.480
I was just thinking about the fact that...

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:58.280
He knew I was losing on purpose.

00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:02.360
So what are you gonna do?

00:14:02.360 --> 00:14:03.680
I'm gonna run it back for a rematch.

00:14:03.680 --> 00:14:04.720
Again?

00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:07.400
Dude, this is like the third time already.

00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:10.160
Won't your fans think you're being a sore loser picking on a kid?

00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:13.240
A guy like me wins through pure skill.

00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:15.120
I don't need anyone throwing the game for me.

00:14:15.760 --> 00:14:18.640
If I didn't throw it and ended up winning again,

00:14:18.640 --> 00:14:21.560
Don't you think his fans would haunt me for the rest of my life?

00:14:21.680 --> 00:14:23.280
You don't have to wait that long.

00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:27.040
I'll make sure my fans trash you right now.

00:14:27.160 --> 00:14:29.360
If you don't agree to a rematch right now...

00:14:29.440 --> 00:14:32.680
At this point, I'd rather hide than get my head bashed in

00:14:32.920 --> 00:14:34.640
Because no matter what...

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:36.360
- There's gotta be a rematch. - there will never be a rematch.

00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:40.520
(I knew you from RoV. You're such an amazing Support.)

00:14:40.560 --> 00:14:42.480
(I'm a fan, and I'm rooting for you.)

00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:47.400
Thank you. I'll do my best to keep improving.

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:51.320
(Knew you from P'Three's channel.)

00:14:54.720 --> 00:14:55.920
(Hey, Derpy Kid. You asleep yet?)

00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:58.120
Whoa, P'Three?

00:14:59.720 --> 00:15:01.680
(What? Did P'Three just DM you?)

00:15:01.920 --> 00:15:03.160
(Oh, P'Three's here.)

00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:06.120
- Uh... I mean... - (Answer him first, Derpy Kid.)

00:15:06.160 --> 00:15:08.680
A lot of P'Three's fans are watching me now.

00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:10.200
Thank you, guys.

00:15:10.240 --> 00:15:11.640
I'm gonna play one last match.

00:15:11.640 --> 00:15:13.640
Does anyone want to join me?

00:15:14.280 --> 00:15:15.920
If you do,

00:15:15.920 --> 00:15:17.600
I'm about to create a room.

00:15:17.960 --> 00:15:19.320
Ready, everyone?

00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:20.640
The room code is...

00:15:20.640 --> 00:15:24.360
850405

00:15:24.520 --> 00:15:27.120
(Derpy Kid, why aren't you answering my text?)

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:28.360
(P'Three's here.)

00:15:28.440 --> 00:15:30.000
(You don't need to give me your time.)

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:31.480
(Spend it with him.)

00:15:31.520 --> 00:15:33.960
(Is something wrong, P'Three? I'm about to go to bed.)

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:36.280
(Are you a 3-year-old? Going to bed at 9 PM?)

00:15:36.440 --> 00:15:38.400
(You were just asking your viewers to play a second ago.)

00:15:39.040 --> 00:15:40.640
Uh, guys...

00:15:40.640 --> 00:15:41.960
I'm getting sleepy now.

00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:43.760
I think I'll head out for today.

00:15:43.760 --> 00:15:45.040
See you next time.

00:15:45.080 --> 00:15:46.080
Bye-bye, everyone.

00:15:53.160 --> 00:15:54.600
(Trying to run away?)

00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:59.000
Gosh, I totally forgot the app is linked to my phone.

00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:03.960
(I know you're trying to delete the app. Don't even try.)

00:16:04.640 --> 00:16:05.640
Is he a stalker or something?

00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:08.040
(No, I'm not, P'Three.)

00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:10.040
(I'm seriously too sleepy right now.)

00:16:10.080 --> 00:16:12.120
(Really? Prove it with a selfie)

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:13.600
(so I know you're not lying.)

00:16:13.800 --> 00:16:15.200
Do I really need to do that?

00:16:20.840 --> 00:16:21.960
Is he messing with me?

00:16:25.800 --> 00:16:28.120
(I'm getting kind of sleepy, too.)

00:16:29.200 --> 00:16:31.240
(What kind of monkey is that? It looks so funny.)

00:16:32.520 --> 00:16:33.440
(A B-Ape.)

00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:37.080
Isn't it supposed to be an ape?

00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:41.640
(Wait, did you mean an ape?)

00:16:42.920 --> 00:16:44.960
(Yeah, it can be a B-Ape, too.)

00:16:45.160 --> 00:16:47.720
(Really? I didn't know that.)

00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:49.920
(Jeez, this is sending me.)

00:16:50.800 --> 00:16:51.840
Sending him?

00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:54.000
(I'm sorry, P'Three.)

00:16:54.880 --> 00:16:57.480
(By the way, did you mean that I should send you something?)

00:17:02.640 --> 00:17:05.440
(Seriously, Derpy Kid?)

00:17:08.160 --> 00:17:09.720
(I'm not really up on today's slang.)

00:17:15.600 --> 00:17:18.240
Gosh, Derpy Kid.

00:17:21.040 --> 00:17:22.040
Sending him?

00:17:24.640 --> 00:17:25.560
What is it?

00:17:26.080 --> 00:17:27.400
He wants me to send him something?

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:29.840
Sending him...

00:17:30.080 --> 00:17:31.000
Send him off?

00:17:31.840 --> 00:17:32.720
Sending him off.

00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:36.280
(Do you think I should wear this on stream?)

00:17:37.400 --> 00:17:40.000
(Do you want to be a monkey that badly?)

00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:41.840
(You dummy, I was just joking.)

00:17:42.120 --> 00:17:43.200
(Oh, were you?)

00:17:44.080 --> 00:17:45.800
(Derpy Kid, I have a question.)

00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:47.480
(How come you never use a cam while streaming?)

00:17:47.520 --> 00:17:49.760
(Oh, I don't have a facecam.)

00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:52.760
(What? You're a streamer without a facecam?)

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:56.280
(My channel doesn't get many viewers anyway.)

00:18:03.160 --> 00:18:05.120
(And I figured whoever does drop in)

00:18:05.280 --> 00:18:07.000
(is probably there for the gameplay.)

00:18:07.200 --> 00:18:08.720
(Nobody would want to see my face.)

00:18:09.400 --> 00:18:10.320
(I would.)

00:18:10.400 --> 00:18:11.400
Mookrata?

00:18:11.680 --> 00:18:12.320
(Wait a minute.)

00:18:12.760 --> 00:18:13.840
(Are you saying)

00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:16.680
(I use a facecam just to show off my looks?)

00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:18.400
So, somtam?

00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:21.280
- Gosh, we just had it yesterday. - No, that's not what I meant.

00:18:21.720 --> 00:18:24.120
I wasn't trying to insult you.

00:18:24.640 --> 00:18:27.000
I was just talking about my viewers.

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:28.040
Who are you talking to?

00:18:29.200 --> 00:18:30.600
I'm starving. Let's go get some food.

00:18:31.120 --> 00:18:32.000
(Send me your address.)

00:18:32.440 --> 00:18:33.640
(I'm buying you a facecam.)

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:36.280
(Come on, there's no need.)

00:18:36.960 --> 00:18:39.600
(I planned on streaming without it anyway.)

00:18:40.400 --> 00:18:42.440
(Come on, don't you wanna give it a try?)

00:18:42.840 --> 00:18:45.160
(When viewers see the streamer's face,)

00:18:45.280 --> 00:18:46.400
(it helps them enjoy the game better.)

00:18:46.400 --> 00:18:48.000
(It's way better than just hearing our voices.)

00:18:50.080 --> 00:18:51.080
Who are you texting?

00:18:51.280 --> 00:18:52.120
You can't stop smiling.

00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:54.600
P'Three!

00:18:54.640 --> 00:18:56.120
You're Thr33Gamer, right?

00:18:56.160 --> 00:18:57.840
You're so handsome in person.

00:18:57.880 --> 00:18:59.280
Can we take a photo together?

00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:00.200
Sure, come on.

00:19:00.280 --> 00:19:01.240
Can you do the cat ears?

00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:03.040
- Sure. Absolutely. - (I get where you're coming from,)

00:19:03.360 --> 00:19:04.400
(but as for me,)

00:19:04.880 --> 00:19:06.520
(I think I'd be more comfortable)

00:19:06.760 --> 00:19:08.840
(if I could keep my life and games separate.)

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:11.600
(I only started streaming because my friends told me to.)

00:19:11.800 --> 00:19:13.480
(They said it would help me be more confident.)

00:19:14.120 --> 00:19:16.920
(But seeing my viewer count grow)

00:19:17.480 --> 00:19:19.440
(makes me want to improve the channel.)

00:19:20.040 --> 00:19:22.400
(And it's all because I met you, P'Three.)

00:19:22.880 --> 00:19:24.240
(Thank you so much.)

00:19:24.720 --> 00:19:25.680
What's with that smile now?

00:19:26.320 --> 00:19:26.960
Mind your own business.

00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:29.560
What do you want? Just eat.

00:19:33.520 --> 00:19:34.520
(I'm tired of texting.)

00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:35.920
(Can we hop on a call instead?)

00:19:41.400 --> 00:19:42.960
(Uh... Sure, sir.)

00:19:44.600 --> 00:19:45.720
(No need to call me sir.)

00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:49.600
You're not as talkative as you were in the chat.

00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:54.160
Then I won't call you that anymore, sir.

00:19:54.680 --> 00:19:55.320
Oh...

00:19:56.240 --> 00:19:58.400
I won't call you "sir" anymore, sir. Oh...

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:00.240
(Sorry, sir. Ugh!)

00:20:01.640 --> 00:20:02.720
What are you even saying?

00:20:04.200 --> 00:20:04.920
What?

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:08.440
(Are you only talkative when you're talking to your partner?)

00:20:10.320 --> 00:20:11.160
No, that's not it.

00:20:11.480 --> 00:20:12.880
I don't even have one.

00:20:13.400 --> 00:20:14.840
I'm still just a student.

00:20:15.240 --> 00:20:16.520
Come on.

00:20:16.800 --> 00:20:19.480
You can be a student and date at the same time, kiddo.

00:20:20.120 --> 00:20:20.920
(Really?)

00:20:23.040 --> 00:20:23.640
So...

00:20:24.680 --> 00:20:25.840
Do you have a partner yet, P'Three?

00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:29.520
I'm looking for one.

00:20:32.280 --> 00:20:33.520
I hope you find them soon.

00:20:35.920 --> 00:20:38.400
Who knows? I might've already found them today.

00:20:40.320 --> 00:20:41.480
I just don't realize it yet.

00:20:43.960 --> 00:20:45.440
Well, that's possible.

00:20:45.480 --> 00:20:47.560
We walk past hundreds of people every day.

00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:52.400
I might've already met you today.

00:20:53.760 --> 00:20:54.600
Me?

00:20:56.120 --> 00:20:57.720
How could you have met me?

00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:02.840
You don't even know what I look like.

00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:06.160
You're right.

00:21:07.240 --> 00:21:10.040
So when do I get to meet you?

00:21:14.200 --> 00:21:14.720
Oh...

00:21:24.280 --> 00:21:26.840
P'Three, I'm getting pretty sleepy.

00:21:27.080 --> 00:21:28.560
I'm going to bed now.

00:21:28.960 --> 00:21:30.120
Goodnight, P'Three.

00:21:52.840 --> 00:21:53.920
(Everything's set. If you're okay, I'll post it right away.)

00:21:53.920 --> 00:21:55.200
(If Derya MK12 loses to Thr33Gamer, he must stream with his cam on.)

00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:57.440
PECHTECH is gonna sponsor you for a whole year?

00:21:58.080 --> 00:21:59.240
That's so sick.

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:03.000
It's not sick, James.

00:22:04.280 --> 00:22:05.440
How is it not?

00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:06.600
Just think about it.

00:22:06.720 --> 00:22:10.160
P'Pech is giving Soh a full year of sponsorship.

00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:11.280
What would he get?

00:22:11.320 --> 00:22:13.440
Upgrading the channel and video quality.

00:22:13.440 --> 00:22:15.560
Getting more income, followers,

00:22:15.600 --> 00:22:16.840
And all kinds of other sponsors.

00:22:16.880 --> 00:22:18.800
Wow, it's all good news.

00:22:19.080 --> 00:22:20.080
Yeah, that's if he wins.

00:22:20.120 --> 00:22:21.760
Have you read what happens if he loses?

00:22:22.240 --> 00:22:23.200
Dammit.

00:22:25.120 --> 00:22:28.440
(If Derya MK12 loses to Thr33Gamer,)

00:22:28.800 --> 00:22:30.680
(he must stream with his cam on.)

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:32.480
Sh*t, with a cam on?

00:22:32.520 --> 00:22:33.680
Yeah, exactly.

00:22:35.880 --> 00:22:37.960
Who the hell came up with this face reveal idea?

00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:39.280
Could it be P'Three?

00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:43.960
Why always me?

00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:46.160
What are you gonna do?

00:22:46.400 --> 00:22:47.240
Are you gonna say yes?

00:22:50.080 --> 00:22:51.640
Hey, don't get so stressed out.

00:22:51.640 --> 00:22:52.920
I'll ask my friend for you.

00:22:55.120 --> 00:22:56.040
What are you doing, Arm?

00:22:56.160 --> 00:22:59.600
He's using AI to calculate your chances of surviving Threenos.

00:23:00.640 --> 00:23:01.440
"Threenos"?

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:04.480
My AI buddy says you only have

00:23:04.560 --> 00:23:06.320
A 45% chance of winning.

00:23:08.080 --> 00:23:09.560
Sh*t.

00:23:09.800 --> 00:23:11.280
It really is always you.

00:23:11.320 --> 00:23:12.960
Hey, but if you get serious,

00:23:13.000 --> 00:23:14.600
No one can beat you.

00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:17.280
If you want this to end, you'll have to fight him one more time.

00:23:17.880 --> 00:23:18.760
Trust me.

00:23:21.440 --> 00:23:22.240
In this game,

00:23:23.000 --> 00:23:25.760
There's no honor among thieves.

00:23:26.920 --> 00:23:28.920
If you want to be a survivor,

00:23:28.920 --> 00:23:31.280
You have to outsmart the hunter.

00:23:32.320 --> 00:23:33.440
How's that? Pretty deep, huh?

00:23:33.880 --> 00:23:34.400
Yeah.

00:23:37.760 --> 00:23:39.080
Thanks a lot, guys.

00:23:47.640 --> 00:23:50.600
(P'Three, did you have anything to do)

00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:52.320
(with P'Pech wanting me to use a facecam?)

00:23:57.120 --> 00:23:58.040
(I'm in.)

00:24:01.840 --> 00:24:04.320
(I didn't suggest it. Sorry for the late reply.)

00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:06.400
(I did talk to him about changing the rules,)

00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:07.520
(but he wouldn't budge.)

00:24:07.600 --> 00:24:09.520
(If you're not okay with it, you don't have to say yes.)

00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:12.280
(Got it. See you, bro.)

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:22.000
Come on, don't be so stressed out.

00:24:22.280 --> 00:24:24.040
We'll help you out, right, James?

00:24:24.080 --> 00:24:25.880
Yeah, we've got your back.

00:24:26.440 --> 00:24:27.040
Yeah.

00:24:39.840 --> 00:24:40.800
Are you Mr. Soh?

00:24:40.840 --> 00:24:41.400
Yes.

00:24:41.600 --> 00:24:42.560
There's a parcel for you.

00:24:45.760 --> 00:24:46.400
Here you go.

00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:47.080
Thank you.

00:24:56.320 --> 00:24:57.880
(FRAGILE)

00:25:10.520 --> 00:25:11.360
If I lose,

00:25:11.920 --> 00:25:13.480
Do I really have to do a face reveal?

00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:26.640
(Unknown: Waiting to see you lose. I just wanna see your face.)

00:25:26.880 --> 00:25:29.800
- (Just do it. You'll lose anyway.) - (I'm sharing this.)

00:25:29.840 --> 00:25:32.920
- (Face reveal. Face reveal.) - (I'm on P'Three's side.)

00:25:32.920 --> 00:25:34.760
- (Got many kills today?) - (Face reveal. Face reveal.)

00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:37.480
- (I'm so invested.) - (We want a face reveal.)

00:25:37.480 --> 00:25:40.920
- (Face reveal. Face reveal.) - (Talk as big as you do off-camera.)

00:25:45.640 --> 00:25:46.880
What are you afraid of, Derpy Kid?

00:25:47.560 --> 00:25:48.720
I'm right here with you.

00:26:00.080 --> 00:26:01.400
If anyone tries to bully you,

00:26:02.000 --> 00:26:04.120
Just let me know. I'll take care of them.

00:26:07.600 --> 00:26:09.440
I know you have your eyes closed.

00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:12.320
Don't you want to open them and look at me?

00:26:48.600 --> 00:26:51.600
So, those who want to see Soh's face reveal,

00:26:51.640 --> 00:26:53.040
Drop a comment and tell me why.

00:26:56.280 --> 00:26:57.600
"Wanna know if he's handsome?"

00:26:57.600 --> 00:26:58.400
Good question.

00:26:58.440 --> 00:26:59.920
How could he be more handsome than me?

00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:07.680
"You want to see his face?"

00:27:07.720 --> 00:27:09.080
Yeah, so do I.

00:27:09.440 --> 00:27:10.760
Alright, alright.

00:27:10.800 --> 00:27:12.440
Calm down. I get it.

00:27:12.600 --> 00:27:14.080
I'll make it happen for you guys.

00:27:14.080 --> 00:27:15.600
Alright? I'll make sure of it.

00:27:15.680 --> 00:27:16.960
But don't pressure him.

00:27:17.040 --> 00:27:18.160
What if he runs away?

00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:21.280
Or you won't get to see me play against that damn bear.

00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:43.160
You'll definitely see it today.

00:27:50.400 --> 00:27:51.600
(Thank you, P'Three.)

00:27:52.120 --> 00:27:54.840
(It felt like you were right next to me,)

00:27:54.920 --> 00:27:56.800
(comforting me the whole time.)

00:28:01.400 --> 00:28:03.160
(Who's texting you? Let me see.)

00:28:03.360 --> 00:28:06.160
(Is it the damn bear? You can't stop smiling.)

00:28:06.680 --> 00:28:09.000
(Gosh, I'm so here for this.)

00:28:10.520 --> 00:28:11.720
Won't tell you.

00:28:26.120 --> 00:28:27.400
(Come on, Soh.)

00:28:27.440 --> 00:28:30.160
(Show the world what you've got and crush this famous streamer.)

00:28:37.800 --> 00:28:39.160
(Are you ready, Soh?)

00:28:40.160 --> 00:28:40.840
I am.

00:29:08.960 --> 00:29:10.840
James, Arm, how's the progress?

00:29:11.000 --> 00:29:12.480
Over halfway. Hurry up.

00:29:16.240 --> 00:29:16.800
Ow.

00:29:16.800 --> 00:29:18.720
Do it properly. Stay focused.

00:29:18.720 --> 00:29:20.080
Sh*t, come help me.

00:29:25.880 --> 00:29:27.000
My heart is racing.

00:29:28.080 --> 00:29:29.560
P'Three is definitely getting close.

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:32.560
Do it faster.

00:29:32.600 --> 00:29:33.880
Do I need to show you how?

00:29:37.280 --> 00:29:38.640
Sh*t, run!

00:29:38.720 --> 00:29:40.960
Where are you?

00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:57.080
Where are you going, Derpy Kid?

00:29:57.560 --> 00:29:59.960
Just let me catch you.

00:30:05.160 --> 00:30:06.920
Where do you think you're going?

00:30:09.320 --> 00:30:12.360
Come and let me catch you, Derpy Kid.

00:30:15.000 --> 00:30:16.600
Let me tell you something.

00:30:16.840 --> 00:30:18.640
About that whole "no camera" thing,

00:30:19.080 --> 00:30:20.360
I can understand that.

00:30:20.720 --> 00:30:25.240
But I'm not gonna throw the game like someone did.

00:30:27.320 --> 00:30:28.200
Take it easy.

00:30:28.200 --> 00:30:29.400
Let's just talk this out.

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:32.120
I'm sorry, P'Three.

00:30:32.200 --> 00:30:34.440
My friends told me there's no honor among thieves in this game.

00:30:34.480 --> 00:30:36.320
I might not be a thief, but I'm among them.

00:30:36.360 --> 00:30:38.120
So, I have to play like one.

00:30:44.880 --> 00:30:46.360
You goddamn bear!

00:30:55.400 --> 00:30:56.360
Help.

00:30:56.400 --> 00:30:57.600
- Help! - James, Arm?

00:30:57.920 --> 00:30:59.280
- Help me out. - Hurry.

00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:03.560
Where are you, Derpy Kid?

00:31:03.600 --> 00:31:04.320
Sh*t.

00:31:07.320 --> 00:31:09.360
Where are you hiding, Derpy Kid?

00:31:15.600 --> 00:31:16.200
Hey,

00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:18.760
Where's your friend?

00:31:18.880 --> 00:31:19.800
I don't know.

00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:20.880
You don't?

00:31:23.600 --> 00:31:24.400
Over there?

00:31:29.400 --> 00:31:30.480
Derpy Kid,

00:31:31.120 --> 00:31:35.240
Do you know why I like playing as the killer?

00:31:40.560 --> 00:31:41.720
It's because...

00:31:43.600 --> 00:31:44.800
I like you,

00:31:47.120 --> 00:31:49.760
Especially when your heart is racing.

00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:00.200
Where is he?

00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:03.000
Hey!

00:32:04.800 --> 00:32:06.680
- Derpy Kid. - Go, go. Quickly.

00:32:07.240 --> 00:32:07.840
Hurry.

00:32:08.520 --> 00:32:09.600
Derpy Kid!

00:32:16.920 --> 00:32:19.360
Where are you going?

00:32:21.880 --> 00:32:23.160
You've got nowhere left to run.

00:32:24.840 --> 00:32:25.800
Come sit right here.

00:32:26.600 --> 00:32:28.960
I'm gonna give you a very warm welcome.

00:32:56.400 --> 00:32:58.560
Don't even think about escaping me.

00:33:00.200 --> 00:33:03.200
Should we keep playing for a bit longer?

00:33:04.040 --> 00:33:04.800
Fine.

00:33:06.040 --> 00:33:06.800
But...

00:33:08.400 --> 00:33:11.400
You need to beg me.

00:33:11.600 --> 00:33:14.000
Make it cute and adorable,

00:33:14.360 --> 00:33:16.000
And I might consider letting you go.

00:33:20.600 --> 00:33:21.160
Well,

00:33:21.480 --> 00:33:23.480
If you're that eager for the face reveal, suit yourself.

00:33:24.240 --> 00:33:25.520
P'Three, please.

00:33:25.600 --> 00:33:27.120
Please let me go.

00:33:27.240 --> 00:33:30.000
Pretty please, P'Three?

00:33:30.200 --> 00:33:32.040
Please, I'm begging you.

00:33:32.480 --> 00:33:33.600
To put it simply,

00:33:33.640 --> 00:33:35.360
There's no honor among thieves.

00:33:44.520 --> 00:33:45.640
P'Three!

00:33:45.680 --> 00:33:47.560
P'Three, no.

00:33:47.600 --> 00:33:49.640
No! No...

00:33:49.840 --> 00:33:51.120
No.

00:34:01.280 --> 00:34:03.440
Soh, you lost. You have to keep your promise.

00:34:03.760 --> 00:34:04.840
A stream...

00:34:05.360 --> 00:34:06.280
With your facecam on.

00:34:06.640 --> 00:34:08.480
(You lost. Now keep your promise.)

00:34:08.720 --> 00:34:10.520
(Turn on your facecam. Everyone's waiting.)

00:34:24.240 --> 00:34:25.760
Do I really have to do it?

00:35:09.480 --> 00:35:11.000
Hello, everyone. It's Soh here.

00:35:15.520 --> 00:35:16.200
(This is...)

00:35:16.840 --> 00:35:18.800
(my first time using a facecam.)

00:35:19.280 --> 00:35:21.800
I might be a little awkward.

00:35:22.160 --> 00:35:24.320
So, please be kind to me.

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:40.800
(Derpy Kid.)

00:35:44.240 --> 00:35:44.960
(Yes?)

00:35:47.280 --> 00:35:50.320
(I just wanted you to know that the reason I wanted to see your face)

00:35:50.440 --> 00:35:52.240
(wasn't about winning.)

00:35:52.800 --> 00:35:54.400
(I just really wanted to know you.)

00:36:06.800 --> 00:36:08.880
(When I'm ready,)

00:36:09.080 --> 00:36:10.640
(you'll be the first person on this channel)

00:36:10.760 --> 00:36:12.280
(to see my real face.)

00:36:28.160 --> 00:36:29.120
(GG.)

00:36:33.960 --> 00:36:35.520
(You, too.)

00:36:36.480 --> 00:36:37.720
(You're the best.)

00:36:44.240 --> 00:36:45.600
(Thank you. Thank you so much.)

00:36:46.120 --> 00:36:46.880
(Oh...)

00:36:48.240 --> 00:36:51.640
(I'm still feeling pretty shy. I'm not really used to this yet.)

00:36:52.520 --> 00:36:53.280
(But...)

00:36:54.640 --> 00:36:55.400
(Uh...)

00:36:56.080 --> 00:36:59.160
(Can you guys slow down the chat a bit?)

00:36:59.200 --> 00:37:00.360
(I can't keep up.)

00:37:08.640 --> 00:37:11.000
The bear head had me dying last night.

00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:12.000
Right, Preaw?

00:37:12.120 --> 00:37:14.000
Totally. He was tricky.

00:37:14.160 --> 00:37:15.280
- Yeah. - What do you think, P'Jack?

00:37:16.240 --> 00:37:17.240
Great reflexes.

00:37:17.360 --> 00:37:18.480
Perfect game sense.

00:37:18.600 --> 00:37:20.280
A true natural-born support.

00:37:20.360 --> 00:37:21.760
Hey, hey, hey.

00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:23.320
You're supposed to give me the spotlight.

00:37:23.360 --> 00:37:24.840
I beat him, you know.

00:37:25.120 --> 00:37:26.120
Fine, whatever.

00:37:26.160 --> 00:37:26.960
P'Toobtub,

00:37:27.080 --> 00:37:29.760
Say something nice about our team captain.

00:37:32.160 --> 00:37:32.760
What?

00:37:34.080 --> 00:37:34.600
Hey.

00:37:35.120 --> 00:37:36.360
Is something wrong, bro?

00:37:38.800 --> 00:37:39.920
For this year's tournament,

00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:41.680
I might...

00:37:42.440 --> 00:37:43.400
Withdraw.

00:37:43.640 --> 00:37:44.560
- What? - What?

00:37:44.640 --> 00:37:45.840
- You'll withdraw? - You'll withdraw?

00:37:47.760 --> 00:37:48.840
Why, bro?

00:37:49.560 --> 00:37:51.040
I'm gonna be a dad soon.

00:37:51.200 --> 00:37:52.040
- What? - What?

00:37:52.200 --> 00:37:53.400
- A dad? - A dad?

00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:57.280
So that means...

00:37:57.320 --> 00:37:58.760
P'Jane, your girlfriend...

00:37:58.960 --> 00:38:00.120
Is she pregnant?

00:38:01.640 --> 00:38:02.560
- Huh? - Huh?

00:38:02.600 --> 00:38:03.720
- With four kids? - With four kids?

00:38:03.800 --> 00:38:05.000
Four months!

00:38:05.840 --> 00:38:07.400
Four kids would stretch her out.

00:38:07.560 --> 00:38:08.800
But does that mean

00:38:08.840 --> 00:38:10.480
You're going to leave B.S. Brothers like this?

00:38:10.520 --> 00:38:11.920
I'm not leaving you guys.

00:38:12.120 --> 00:38:13.440
I'm just stepping behind the scenes

00:38:13.480 --> 00:38:15.080
To look at the big picture and be your coach.

00:38:15.120 --> 00:38:17.560
Do you know which position our team is missing?

00:38:19.240 --> 00:38:20.000
The Support.

00:38:20.320 --> 00:38:20.880
Correct.

00:38:21.440 --> 00:38:23.240
And where are we going to find one?

00:38:35.760 --> 00:38:37.320
I think I have someone in mind.

00:38:40.280 --> 00:38:41.680
Hello, everyone.

00:38:42.480 --> 00:38:43.280
It's me.

00:38:48.960 --> 00:38:50.520
(I need to talk to you about something important.)

00:38:50.680 --> 00:38:51.960
(Can we meet?)

00:38:55.560 --> 00:38:56.320
(Where?)

00:38:57.200 --> 00:38:59.600
(If you don't mind, I'll come over to your room.)

00:39:01.960 --> 00:39:03.400
(I already got your address from P'Pech.)

00:39:03.760 --> 00:39:05.480
(All that's left is for you to give me permission to come over.)

00:39:13.600 --> 00:39:14.640
Hey, we're heading out now.

00:39:14.800 --> 00:39:16.240
Hey, don't go yet.

00:39:17.280 --> 00:39:18.840
- What's up? - Uh, I'll be right back.

00:39:18.880 --> 00:39:20.600
Just a second, okay?

00:39:26.960 --> 00:39:27.680
P'Three...

00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:29.680
He asked to come to my room.

00:39:29.720 --> 00:39:30.440
- What? - What?

00:39:30.560 --> 00:39:31.840
- To your room? - To your room?

00:39:32.480 --> 00:39:34.440
No, no, no. Just turn him down, Soh.

00:39:34.480 --> 00:39:36.160
Asking to come over when you aren't even close yet?

00:39:36.560 --> 00:39:37.880
Isn't that a bit dangerous?

00:39:38.040 --> 00:39:38.520
Look at you.

00:39:39.480 --> 00:39:40.800
Are you guys already close?

00:39:41.240 --> 00:39:42.160
Not at all.

00:39:43.960 --> 00:39:46.080
You can let him come over if you're okay with it,

00:39:46.080 --> 00:39:47.800
And we'll keep you company, okay?

00:39:50.280 --> 00:39:52.000
Just set a date and time with him.

00:39:52.760 --> 00:39:53.560
Alright, we're off.

00:39:54.080 --> 00:39:56.360
I still have to help Arm carry cases of water up to his room.

00:39:56.440 --> 00:39:57.800
Look at him. He's so tiny.

00:39:59.800 --> 00:40:00.800
I'll go drop you off.

00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:06.760
I'm going to drop my friends off first.

00:40:06.760 --> 00:40:07.880
Be back in a bit.

00:40:13.200 --> 00:40:16.320
(What day and what time do you want to meet?)

00:40:25.600 --> 00:40:26.400
Sorry, guys.

00:40:26.400 --> 00:40:29.120
I was just talking with my friends.

00:40:33.760 --> 00:40:34.640
Just a second, guys.

00:40:34.640 --> 00:40:37.120
I think they forgot something.

00:40:57.760 --> 00:40:58.960
Hello, ma...

00:41:01.440 --> 00:41:03.080
Hello, ma boy.

00:41:05.800 --> 00:41:07.520
(Wait, was that P'Three's voice?)

00:41:07.520 --> 00:41:09.000
(Did anyone else hear that?)

00:41:09.040 --> 00:41:10.320
Hello, ma fans.

00:41:10.440 --> 00:41:12.080
It's your one and only Three right here.

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:18.520
(Oops, what are you doing in Soh's room?)

00:41:19.120 --> 00:41:21.200
You want to know what I'm doing here?

00:41:22.400 --> 00:41:23.760
Hmm...

00:41:25.120 --> 00:41:26.880
Maybe to ask him to be my boyfriend.

00:41:33.080 --> 00:41:34.320
If you don't shut down your PC properly,

00:41:34.400 --> 00:41:35.840
It might crash, kiddo.

00:41:37.960 --> 00:41:38.640
Uh...

00:41:39.520 --> 00:41:41.360
Uh, it won't crash.

00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:42.840
Anyway,

00:41:43.160 --> 00:41:44.160
Are you...

00:41:44.800 --> 00:41:46.400
Really here to ask me to be your boyfriend?

00:41:54.840 --> 00:41:56.440
No, I was just messing with you.

00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:00.240
Whoa, whoa, seriously?

00:42:01.680 --> 00:42:04.160
P'Three, don't mess with me like that.

00:42:04.360 --> 00:42:05.040
Why can't I?

00:42:07.520 --> 00:42:09.040
Do you actually want me to do it for real?

00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:10.640
No.

00:42:11.080 --> 00:42:13.760
So, now that you've come all this way,

00:42:13.800 --> 00:42:15.560
What's the important thing you want to talk about?

00:42:19.880 --> 00:42:21.680
Well, before we get to that,

00:42:22.160 --> 00:42:23.200
Can you...

00:42:25.720 --> 00:42:27.040
Take off that bear head first?

00:42:31.320 --> 00:42:35.160
Can't we just talk like this?

00:42:37.280 --> 00:42:38.960
Look, the reason I'm here talking to you

00:42:39.080 --> 00:42:40.840
Is because I trust you a lot.

00:42:42.120 --> 00:42:43.880
I want you to trust me as well.

00:42:53.640 --> 00:42:56.000
Hey, it's alright.

00:42:56.080 --> 00:42:58.440
We can do it your way.

00:42:58.800 --> 00:43:00.040
I'll just wait until you're ready.

00:43:03.880 --> 00:43:05.080
It's okay, P'Three.

00:43:08.440 --> 00:43:09.560
If it's you,

00:43:10.360 --> 00:43:11.840
I think I'm ready.

00:43:32.200 --> 00:43:33.600
Come here, let me help you.

00:43:57.360 --> 00:43:58.880
Is there something on my face?

00:44:02.600 --> 00:44:03.800
It's your champion aura.

00:44:05.240 --> 00:44:06.280
My champion aura?

00:44:10.120 --> 00:44:11.200
Come join me.

00:44:41.360 --> 00:44:42.560
Hello, ma boy.

00:44:42.560 --> 00:44:44.760
Hello, ma boy!

00:44:44.960 --> 00:44:46.240
Hello, ma boy.

00:44:46.400 --> 00:44:46.840
Hello.

00:44:46.840 --> 00:44:47.880
Three, you're being so cringe.

00:44:47.880 --> 00:44:48.440
Hello.

00:44:49.480 --> 00:44:51.880
Hello, ma boy.

00:44:52.360 --> 00:44:55.480
What do you think would happen if P'Three and Soh were alone together?

00:44:56.080 --> 00:44:58.120
Man, I don't even want to imagine it.

00:44:58.240 --> 00:45:00.440
I bet P'Three would make Soh so nervous he'd literally freeze up.

00:45:00.440 --> 00:45:02.320
Come on, you're exaggerating.

00:45:03.600 --> 00:45:07.000
But I think if P'Three approaches him sincerely,

00:45:07.280 --> 00:45:09.000
He'll eventually open up, won't he?

00:45:09.240 --> 00:45:10.640
- I guess. - Yeah.

00:45:17.120 --> 00:45:18.040
Are you coming?

00:45:18.840 --> 00:45:20.040
I already have a boyfriend.

00:45:21.320 --> 00:45:21.880
What the hell?

00:45:23.760 --> 00:45:25.000
I'm not coming.

00:45:26.120 --> 00:45:27.040
She's weird.

00:45:30.360 --> 00:45:31.400
Who's he calling weird?

00:46:03.120 --> 00:46:04.680
Hello, ma...

